{"lemma":"مُثَنَّياتِ","slug":"مُثَنَّياتِ","root":"ث.ن.#","root_slug":"ث-ن-_","root_link":"/words/roots/ث-ن-_","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"مُثَنَّى","root":"ثني","pos":"N","occurrence_count":3},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["adj"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n4783","n4786","n4787"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%85%D9%8F%D8%AB%D9%8E%D9%86%D9%8E%D9%91%D9%8A%D8%A7%D8%AA%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"bent, folded, kinked, flexed"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Derived from the passive participle of ثَنَى (ṯanā, “to bend”)."},"ipa":["/maθ.nijj/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n4783","headword_ar":"مَثْنَى","root":"vnY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vunaA='u","text_ar":"ثُنَا=ءُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Two and two; two and two together;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two at a time and two at a time"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: they are imperfectly decl., in like manner as ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mavolavu","text_ar":"مَثْلَثُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vulaAvu","text_ar":"ثُلَاثُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", as explained in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vlv","text_ar":"ثلث"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S, TA;) [because] changed from the original form of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AivonaAni A@vonaAni","text_ar":"اِثْنَانِ ا@ثْنَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (T, Mgh, TA;) or because of their having the quality of epithets and deviating from the original form of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AivonaAni","text_ar":"اِثْنَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (Sb, S in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vlv","text_ar":"ثلث"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.;) or because they deviate from their original as to the letter and the meaning; the original word being changed as above stated, and the meaning being changed to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AivonaAni A@vonaAni","text_ar":"اِثْنَانِ ا@ثْنَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S ibid.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAw^uwA mavonaY","text_ar":"جَاوُوا مَثْنَى"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vunaA='a","text_ar":"ثُنَا=ءَ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mavonaY mavonaY","text_ar":"مَثْنَى مَثْنَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S,) but this is a repetition of the word only, not of the meaning, (Mgh,) and in like manner one says of women, (M, K, *) i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They came two"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K.) And it is said in a trad.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SalaApu All~ayoli mavonaY mavonaY","text_ar":"صَلَاةُ اللَّيْلِ مَثْنَى مَثْنَى"},{"kind":"text","text":", i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The prayer of night is two rek'ahs"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"two rek'ahs"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakoEataAni rakoEataAni","text_ar":"رَكْعَتَانِ رَكْعَتَانِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"). (TA.) [See also other exs. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vulaAvu","text_ar":"ثُلَاثُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mavonaY AlA^ayaAdiY","text_ar":"مَثْنَى الاَيَادِى"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The repeating a benefit,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"benefaction;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"reiterating it; conferring it twice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"thrice;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, T, K;) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"twice,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"more than twice:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the shares remaining of the slaughtered camel"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A'Obeyd, T, S, M, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the game called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almayosir","text_ar":"المَيْسِر"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A'Obeyd, T, S, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"which shares a bountiful man used to purchase, and give for food to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aboraAm","text_ar":"اَبْرَام"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A'Obeyd, T, S, M, K,) i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"those who took no part in the game, not contributing:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the taking a portion time after time."},{"kind":"text","text":"(AA, T, S, M.) ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mavaAnK","text_ar":"مَثَانٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mavonFY","text_ar":"مَثْنًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"as signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A place of doubling,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"folding"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.: and hence means ―         -b4- ] The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"knees"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"elbows"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a horse or similar beast. (T, K.) ―         -b5-  And The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bends"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a valley. (T, K. See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vinoYN","text_ar":"ثِنْىٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b6-  And, as pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mavonFY","text_ar":"مَثْنًى"},{"kind":"text","text":", The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"chords of the lute that are after the first:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mvnY","text_ar":"مثنى"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a chord"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a lute"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"composed of two twists:"},{"kind":"text","text":"or, as some say, the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"second chord."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Har p. 244. See"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mavolavN","text_ar":"مَثْلَثٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mavonFY","text_ar":"مَثْنًى"},{"kind":"text","text":"also signifies The"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zimaAm","text_ar":"زِمَام"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"noserein"},{"kind":"text","text":"] of a she-camel: and Er-Rághib says that the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mvnAp","text_ar":"مثناة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e. ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mavonaAp","text_ar":"مَثْنَاة","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"or ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mivonaAp","text_ar":"مِثْنَاة","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"doubled,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"folded, part of the extremity of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"zimaAm","text_ar":"زِمَام"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmavaAniY","text_ar":"المَثَانِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"as relating to the Kur-án is pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mavonFY","text_ar":"مَثْنًى"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Mgh,) or of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mavonaApN","text_ar":"مَثْنَاةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (AHeyth, T, Mgh:) it has three applications, accord. to A'Obeyd: (T, Mgh:) it signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The Kur-án altogether;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A'Obeyd, T, S, M, Mgh, K;) so in the Kur xxxix 24; (A'Obeyd, T, Mgh;) meaning that the mention of reward and punishment is repeated, or reiterated, in it; (Fr, T;) or so called because the verse of mercy is conjoined with that of punishment; (S;) or because narratives and promises and threats are repeated in it; or because one peruses it repeatedly without being wearied: (Mgh:) or it signifies, (M, K,) or signifies also, (A'Obeyd, T, S, Mgh,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the first chapter,"},{"kind":"text","text":"called]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faAtiHap","text_ar":"فَاتِحَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A'Obeyd, T, S, M, Mgh,) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHamodu","text_ar":"الحَمْدُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) which means the same; (TA;) so in the Kur xv. 87; (A'Obeyd, T, Mgh;) because it is repeated, or recited twice, in every [act of prayer termed a]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"rakoEap","text_ar":"رَكْعَة"},{"kind":"text","text":", (Fr, Zj, AHeyth, T, S,) or with every chapter, (Th, M,) or in every prayer; (Mgh;) or because containing praise of God: (Zj, T, Mgh:) [but see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~aboEu AlmavaAniY","text_ar":"السَّبْعُ المَثَانِى"},{"kind":"text","text":"voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saboEapN","text_ar":"سَبْعَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] or it signifies, (M, K,) or signifies also, (A'Obeyd, T, S, Mgh,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the chapters that are less than those containing a hundred verses,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, Mgh,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"that are less than the long ones"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~uwal","text_ar":"الطُّوَل"},{"kind":"text","text":", q. v.),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and less than those containing a hundred verses,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A'Obeyd, T, K, but in [most of] the copies of the K"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duwna AlmiA^atayoni","text_ar":"دُونَ المِاَتَيْنِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is put in the place of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"duwna Almiy^iyna","text_ar":"دُونَ المِيِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is the right reading, TA,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and more than"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"those of the portion called"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mufaS~al","text_ar":"مُفَصَّل"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A'Obeyd, T, Mgh, K,) as is related on the authority of the Prophet by Ibn-Mes'ood and 'Othmán and Ibn- 'Abbás; (AHeyth, T;) because, (Mgh,) or as though, (T,) occupying the second place after those containing a hundred verses: (T, Mgh:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the chapters,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"six and twenty in number,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"entitled"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHaj~","text_ar":"الحَجّ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlqaSaS","text_ar":"القَصَص"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~amol","text_ar":"النَّمْل"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~uwr","text_ar":"النُّور"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^anofaAl","text_ar":"الاَنْفَال"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maroyam","text_ar":"مَرْيَم"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEanokabuwt","text_ar":"العَنْكَبُوت"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~uwm","text_ar":"الرُّوم"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yaAsiyn","text_ar":"يَاسِين"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlfuroqaAn","text_ar":"الفُرْقَان"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHijor","text_ar":"الحِجْر"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alr~aEod","text_ar":"الرَّعْد"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sabaA","text_ar":"سَبَا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmalaAy^ikap","text_ar":"المَلَايِكَة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_iboraAhiym","text_ar":"اـِبْرَاهِيم"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"SaAd","text_ar":"صَاد"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muHam~ad","text_ar":"مُحَمَّد"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"luqom`n","text_ar":"لُقْمٰن"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alguraf","text_ar":"الغُرَف"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almuw^omin","text_ar":"المُوْمِن"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alz~uxoruf","text_ar":"الزُّخْرُف"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~ajodap","text_ar":"السَّجْدَة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aHoqaAf","text_ar":"الاَحْقَاف"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AljaAviyap","text_ar":"الجَاثِيَة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ald~uxaAn","text_ar":"الدُّخَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^aHozaAb","text_ar":"الاَحْزَاب"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) which last has been omitted by the copyists of the T: (TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the chapters of which the first is the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baqarap","text_ar":"بَقَرَة"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and the last is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"baraA='ap","text_ar":"بَرَا=ءَة"},{"kind":"text","text":": or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what is repeated, of the Kur-án, time after time."},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K.)"}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","T","M","K","AHeyth","Fr","Zj","Th","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n4786","headword_ar":"مُثَنًّى","root":"vnY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[pass. part. n. of 2. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Dualized:"},{"kind":"text","text":"a"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dual."},{"kind":"text","text":"―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muvan~aApN fawoqiy~apN","text_ar":"مُثَنَّاةٌ فَوْقِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Marked with two points above:"},{"kind":"text","text":"an epithet added to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tA='","text_ar":"تا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"to prevent its being mistaken for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bA='","text_ar":"با=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vA='","text_ar":"ثا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yA='","text_ar":"يا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":". And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muvan~aApN taHotiy~apN","text_ar":"مُثَنَّاةٌ تَحْتِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Marked with two points below:"},{"kind":"text","text":"an epithet added to"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yA='","text_ar":"يا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"to prevent its being mistaken for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"bA='","text_ar":"با=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tA='","text_ar":"تا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vA='","text_ar":"ثا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~awylu Almuvan~aY","text_ar":"الطَّويلُ المُثَنَّى"},{"kind":"text","text":"(assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That which passes away"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"out of sight,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"disappears,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by length;"},{"kind":"text","text":"mostly used of a thing that is long without breadth. (TA.)"}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n4787","headword_ar":"مَثْنِىٌّ","root":"vnY","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"[pass. part. n. of 1;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Doubled"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"folded"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.] ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroDN mavoniy~apN","text_ar":"اَرْضٌ مَثْنِيَّةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Land,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"ground, turned over twice for sowing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"cultivating."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mgh, and A and TA in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vlv","text_ar":"ثلث"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":[]}]},"classical_definitions":null}